Image tools

In [3]:
def load_images() -> pd.DataFrame:
    df:pd.DataFrame = pd.read_csv(IMAGES_MWTADATA_PATH)
    return df[(df["height"] >= 1000) & (df["width"] >= 1000)] 

def get_image_paths(df: pd.DataFrame, root_dir: Path) -> list[str]:
    return [str(root_dir / path) for path in df["path"]]

def insert_images(engine: Engine, images: list["Img"]) -> None:
    with Session(engine) as session:
        session.add_all(images)
        session.commit()

def batched(iterable, n):
    it = iter(iterable)
    while True:
        batch = tuple(islice(it, n))
        if not batch:
            break
        yield batch

def vectorize_images(engine: Engine, model: SentenceTransformer, image_paths: list[str]) -> None:
    with tqdm(total=MAX_IMAGES) as pbar:
        for images_paths_batch in batched(image_paths[:MAX_IMAGES], BATCH_SIZE):           
            images = [Image.open(path).convert("RGB") for path in images_paths_batch]
            embeddings = model.encode(images, convert_to_numpy=True)
            imgs = [
                Img(image_path=path, embedding=embedding.tolist())
                for path, embedding in zip(images_paths_batch, embeddings)
            ]
            insert_images(engine, imgs)
            pbar.update(len(imgs))

class Base(DeclarativeBase):
    pass

class Img(Base):
    __tablename__ = "images_homework_lab_2"
    __table_args__ = {'extend_existing': True}
    
    VECTOR_LENGTH: int = CLIP_VIT_B_32_VECTOR_LEN 
    
    id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(Integer, primary_key=True, autoincrement=True)
    image_path: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(256))
    embedding: Mapped[list[float]] = mapped_column(Vector(VECTOR_LENGTH))

Image search

In [4]:
class ImageSearch:
    def __init__(self, engine, model):
        self.engine = engine
        self.model = model
        
    def __call__(self, image_description: str, k: int):
        found_images = self.find_similar_images(image_description, k)
        self.display_images(found_images, k)

    def find_similar_images(self, image_description: str, k: int):
        image_embedding = self.model.encode(image_description).tolist()
        with Session(self.engine) as session:
            query = (
                select(Img)
                .order_by(Img.embedding.cosine_distance(image_embedding))
                .limit(k)
            )
            result = session.execute(query, execution_options={"prebuffer_rows": True})
            return [img.image_path for img in result.scalars().all()]
    
    def display_images(self, images, k):
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, k, figsize=(15, 5))

        for i, img_path in enumerate(images):
            img = Image.open(img_path)
            axes[i].imshow(img)
            axes[i].axis("off")
            axes[i].set_title(f"Image {i+1}")

        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
